{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In an era where digital content is inherently multimodal, the ability of LLMs to interpret and generate across different media types is crucial for a range of applications, from more accessible information retrieval systems to advanced interactive AI agents [9].",
    "Moreover, the integration of multimodal data presents a unique opportunity to improve the model's understanding of context, nuance, and the subtleties of human communication, thereby making AI interactions more natural and intuitive [1],The corresponding author is Farizal Hamzah (farizal hamzah 1989@outlook.com) [9].",
    "However, the task is far from trivial, as it involves not just the technical challenges of processing and integrating diverse data types but also the conceptual challenge of how different modes of information complement and inform each other.Historically, advancements in LLMs have been driven by innovations in model architecture, training procedures, and data handling techniques.",
    "Models like GPT-3 and its successors demonstrated how scaling up model size and training data could yield qualitative improvements in language understanding and generation.",
    "Yet, as these models grow larger, diminishing returns on textual tasks become apparent, underscoring the need for a paradigm shift towards multimodal learning [1]."
  ],
